<br>
Every 'counter' to SoS I've ever heard of involves the Minstrel having already burned their SoS. Well, that doesn't cut much water if there are two Minstrels involved and they alternate their timers intelligently. Three, and the only way you will kill them is by burning their ISPs to the ground in the middle of a raid.<br>
<br>
And, IMHO, arson is not a viable counter for most players.<br>
<br>
I've heard a lot of Minstrels say, &quot;Well, if SoS were interruptible or counterable, it wouldn't be good for anything!&quot; True enough. That whole RA is flawed beyond repair. Shouldn't ever have existed, can't work in any form.<br>
<br>
Eventually, it will be nerfed so that it WILL be interruptable, or it'll only increase group speed by 50%, or...whatever, and then all the Minstrels who bought it will be rightfully pissed that their primary RA is suddenly useless.<br>
<br>
Incredible lack of foresight, shouldn't ever have made it out of test. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufenrisfil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fenrisfil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/20/02 1:35:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=171.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> &quot;No, you're wrong. If they take three forts they're going to DF. If they take five forts you'd better get your ass to the frontier to defend your relics. Nuff said.&quot;<br>
