Nuff said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Unfortunately, they are using realm abilities to balance classes. See Hidden is a perfect example.&quot;<br>
<br>
Well, sadly you are correct, and Mythics refusal to answer direct questions about it prooves that. However it's certainly not how it should be. Also I suspect the base skills will continue to be balanced and improved on weaker classes so that at some point they will be balance with the realm skills making some classes uber. Then maybe they may balance them. *shrug*<br>
<br>
Still as I said it's not how it should be and until mythic makes an official statement on it we should continue to treat it as if it is seperate for the sake of reasoning with them for nerfing/improvmenets.<br>
<br>
&quot;Personally, I think that all 3 realms should get this ability.&quot;<br>
<br>
I couldn't agree more. I think all realms should have access to similar classes unique abilities in an either/or situation. That would truly force them to be balanced and also mean players can have more inderviduality rather then just have realm skills as an extension of the cookie cutter syndrome of their class limitations.<br>
<br>
I am certain if they said to minstrels, skalds and bards you can have any one of SoS, FoG, or the bardic group heal, they would *all* without exception choose SoS. So mythic would have to make the other two more appealing, and if they did (or nerf SoS) no one could complain because it'd effect all realms evenly.<br>
